choices.text:
why does this command give error Permission denied (publickey):

ssh -i \“~/UserKey.pem" -C -L 25900:localhost:5900 ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com
It seems like you are trying to connect to an AWS EC2 instance using a public key file, but you do not have permission to access the file or the instance. You may need to check if the file is correctly uploaded and configured in your SSH settings, or if you have permission to access the instance through its IP address instead of using a public key file.
